        "opal/4.3.8.1.txt",
        rule="DataStore is a byte table addressed by row number, and byte-table Get returns requested rows as Bytes ordered from lowest row to highest. Opal says the initial DataStore content is vendor-unique, so unwritten bytes in a sparse window are not predictable. However, after a successful Set writes Bytes beginning at a specific Where.Row, those written bytes have fixed row positions. Therefore a later successful explicit Get window may contain arbitrary VU bytes outside the written positions, but it must be long enough to include the written rows and must place the known bytes at their corresponding offsets inside the returned window.",
