        rule="Opal preconfigures DataStore Get and Set through ACE_DataStore_Get_All and ACE_DataStore_Set_All, initially with BooleanExpr Admins, and states that the DataStore access-control settings are personalizable. The ACE BooleanExpr column is modifiable through Set and may name individual authority object references. Opal User1 is an initially disabled individual Password authority with credential C_PIN_User1; after Admin1 enables User1, sets its C_PIN, and personalizes the relevant DataStore ACE(s) to User1, a User1-authenticated Locking SP session may perform only the DataStore operations covered by those ACEs. Successful User1 DataStore Set writes known bytes to the byte table, and a later authorized DataStore Get must return the most recent written bytes.",
