        "opal/4.3.1.9.txt",
        "opal/5.1.1.2.txt",
        rule="DataStore is a byte table whose Get and Set ACLs are separate and personalizable. Byte-table Set writes Bytes beginning at Where.Row or row zero when Where is omitted, and byte-table Get returns requested bytes in row order. A byte-table Get without satisfied access control returns a SUCCESS response with an empty results list. A Set whose access control is not satisfied fails with NOT_AUTHORIZED and the requested changes fail as a whole. Therefore long trajectories with interleaved Admin/User writes must preserve exact byte offsets, Set-only User1 writes must be visible to a later Admin Get but not to User1 Get, later Get ACE personalization can enable User1 reads, and a failed User1 Set must not change bytes seen by a later Admin Get.",
