        rule="An ACE BooleanExpr is the single Boolean expression that authorizes the ACE, and the BooleanExpr column is modified by Set. Opal preconfigures DataStore Get and Set associations to use ACE_DataStore_Get_All and ACE_DataStore_Set_All, whose initial BooleanExpr values are Admins, and says the DataStore access-control settings are personalizable. Therefore after a successful Set changes either DataStore ACE BooleanExpr to User1, that ACE is satisfied by User1 and no longer by Admins unless Admins remains in the expression. Unauthorized byte-table Get returns SUCCESS with an empty result list, while unauthorized Set fails with NOT_AUTHORIZED and makes no changes.",
