        "opal/5.1.1.2.txt",
        "opal/5.3.1.1.2.txt",
        rule="DataStore is a byte table whose Set method writes Bytes beginning at Where.Row or row zero, and whose Get method returns explicitly requested row ranges in byte order. DataStore Get and Set use separate personalizable ACE BooleanExpr cells; changing an ACE BooleanExpr replaces the prior expression. Unauthorized DataStore Get returns SUCCESS with an empty result list, while unauthorized Set fails and makes no table changes. If MandatoryWriteGranularity is observed, DataStore Set start row and byte length must align to that granularity. Therefore long trajectories that alternate Admin and User1 authority, replace Set/Get ACEs, perform partial overwrites, and include failed unauthorized or unaligned writes must preserve the exact byte payload visible to the currently authorized reader.",
