        rule="DataStore is a Locking SP byte table. For byte-table Set, the Values parameter is the Bytes option and the Where.Row parameter, or raw startRow notation, identifies the byte offset where the Bytes payload begins. These are semantic parameters, so a log representation that nests Bytes under Values or represents Values as a raw tuple still encodes the same byte-table payload. Byte-table Get over explicit startRow/endRow returns the requested bytes in increasing row order. Therefore overlapping successful DataStore Sets using top-level Bytes, nested Values.Bytes, list-form Values, and raw Values tuples must compose into one current byte-table payload, and later explicit Get windows must return exact slices of that payload.",
