        "opal/5.3.1.1.2.txt",
        rule="DataStore is a Locking SP byte table. Byte-table Set writes Bytes beginning at Where.Row, or at row zero when Where is omitted, and raw startRow syntax identifies the same byte offset. Byte-table Get over explicit startRow/endRow returns the requested bytes in row order. Opal preconfigures DataStore Get and Set AccessControl rows with separate personalizable ACEs, initially Admins; changing an ACE BooleanExpr replaces the previous expression. Unauthorized byte-table Get succeeds with an empty result list, unauthorized Set fails with NOT_AUTHORIZED, and any failed Set or mandatory-granularity violation leaves the stored bytes unchanged. Therefore split Get/Set ACE trajectories must preserve exact byte offsets across structured writes, raw writes, omitted-Where prefix writes, no-op Sets, Set ACE revocation, and aligned/unaligned mandatory-granularity attempts.",
