        "opal/5.1.1.2.txt",
        rule="ACE BooleanExpr values are Boolean expressions of authorities, and an ACE is satisfied only when the expression evaluates True for the currently authenticated authorities. The ACE BooleanExpr column is host-modifiable through Set, which returns an empty list on success. Opal specifically requires support for the values Admins and Admins OR UserMMMM in each ACE_C_PIN_UserMMMM_Set_PIN row. The Locking SP C_PIN_User1/Set access association uses ACE_C_PIN_User1_Set_PIN for the PIN column. Therefore Admins-only personalization prevents User1 from changing its own PIN, while Admins OR User1 permits User1 after the authority is enabled and its C_PIN is set.",
