        rule="Opal requires User1 through User8 in the Locking SP Authority table and defines C_PIN_UserMMMM, Authority_UserMMMM, ACE_C_PIN_UserMMMM_Set_PIN, and ACE_UserMMMM_Set_CommonName preconfiguration patterns. An Admin session can enable an individual UserMMMM authority and set its C_PIN. ACE_C_PIN_UserMMMM_Set_PIN supports Admins OR UserMMMM in BooleanExpr and covers only the PIN column; the Core ACE Columns cell limits the cells to which an ACE applies. Therefore when UserMMMM authenticates, that ACE can authorize C_PIN_UserMMMM PIN changes but not TryLimit/Tries/Persistence changes. Core Set table modification rules say a Set fails as a whole if access control does not permit some attempted cell change, so mixed PIN+TryLimit changes are not partially successful. Because GetACL returns the AccessControl ACL column rather than the current ACE BooleanExpr, personalizing the ACE does not replace the C_PIN_UserMMMM/Set ACL uidref.",
