        "opal/4.3.1.9.txt",
        rule="Opal requires User1 through User8 and defines UserMMMM Authority, C_PIN, and ACE_C_PIN_UserMMMM_Set_PIN rows. C_PIN.TryLimit/Tries count failed password authentication attempts and successful authentication or successful PIN modification resets Tries to 0; TryLimit=0 keeps Tries at 0, while a nonzero TryLimit clamps Tries at the limit and blocks further authentication until reset. Authority.Limit/Uses are a separate successful-authentication counter: failed Proof or failed StartSession does not increment Uses, successful Proof and successful StartSession increment Uses, and once Uses reaches a nonzero Limit the authority is no longer authenticatable. ACE_C_PIN_UserMMMM_Set_PIN covers only the PIN cell, so UserMMMM self PIN modification can reset Tries without changing TryLimit or Authority.Uses.",
