        rule="DataStore is a Locking SP byte table whose Get and Set AccessControl rows are separate and personalizable. Byte-table Get returns the requested row window in byte order, with omitted startRow defaulting to the first row and omitted endRow defaulting to the last row. If the current authority does not satisfy the byte-table Get ACE, Get returns SUCCESS with an empty result list, not the stored bytes. Byte-table Set writes Bytes beginning at Where.Row or row zero, and a failed unauthorized Set makes no changes. Therefore long traces that replace the Get ACE between Admins/User1/OR values and keep the Set ACE independent must preserve exact authorized read windows, empty unauthorized read windows, and non-mutated payload after failed writes.",
