        rule="The AccessControl table stores rows for access control associations and separate meta-ACL columns for AddACE, RemoveACE, GetACL, and DeleteMethod on each association, but it does not have rows representing the meta-ACL methods themselves. The fail rules for GetACL, AddACE, RemoveACE, and DeleteMethod each require failure when the InvokingID/MethodID combination does not exist. Therefore AccessControl-table meta-method invocations that name InvokingID=AccessControl and MethodID equal to GetACL, AddACE, RemoveACE, or DeleteMethod cannot report SUCCESS, even in an Admins-authorized session.",
