        rule="AccessControl rows are unique InvokingID/MethodID associations with ACL, method logging, meta-method logging, and LogTo cells. The ACL column is returned only by GetACL, so direct Get may omit ACL from a requested mixed range. The other readable cells still identify and constrain the returned row. In Opal Locking SP preconfiguration, issued rows such as C_PIN_User1 Set and MBRControl Get/Set show empty/default Log, AddACELog, RemoveACELog, GetACLLog, DeleteMethodLog, and LogTo cells. Therefore a successful direct AccessControl.Get over InvokingID through LogTo for those rows cannot return invented LogSuccess, LogFail, LogAlways, or a non-default LogList uidref while otherwise self-identifying the same issued row.",
