        rule="AccessControl rows are unique associations identified by InvokingID and MethodID. Direct Get of readable AccessControl identity columns must therefore return the row's actual InvokingID and MethodID, while GetACL retrieves the ACL for that exact same association. In Opal Locking SP preconfiguration, MBRControl.Get and MBRControl.Set share InvokingID 00 00 08 03 00 00 00 01 but are separate AccessControl rows with MethodID Get versus Set and distinct ACL lists: Get uses ACE_Anybody, while Set uses ACE_MBRControl_Admins_Set plus ACE_MBRControl_Set_DoneToDOR. Therefore a successful direct Get cannot swap Get and Set MethodID values, and a successful GetACL cannot return the sibling method's ACL.",
