        "core/5.3.4.3.3.txt",
        "opal/4.3.1.6.txt",
        "opal/4.3.1.7.txt",
        "opal/4.3.8.1.txt",
        rule="GetACL retrieves the ACL column of an AccessControl association and returns that list of ACE uidrefs. Separately, each ACE row has a BooleanExpr column that can be modified by ACE.Set. Changing an ACE BooleanExpr changes whether that ACE is satisfied for authorization, but it does not replace the ACE uidref stored in an AccessControl ACL column. Therefore after personalizing preconfigured ACE rows such as DataStore Get/Set, C_PIN_User1 Set, Locking_Range1 Get/Set, MBRControl Set, or K_AES_Mode, GetACL for the associated method must still return the same ACE uidrefs unless AddACE/RemoveACE changed the ACL itself.",
