        rule="LockingInfo.MaxRanges defines the maximum number of supportable non-global LBA ranges. Opal requires a minimum of eight, but a larger observed MaxRanges value indicates additional range IDs are within the supported range count. Therefore after observing MaxRanges=9, Range9 direct operations and Range9/K_AES Range9 GetACL responses are not excluded by the range count. If such a row/key is present and the returned ACL list matches the Opal RangeNNNN pattern, a successful response can be protocol-compliant.",
