        rule="LockingInfo.MaxRanges is the supported non-global locking range count. Opal requires at least eight non-global ranges, while higher RangeNNNN and K_AES RangeNNNN rows are optional and bounded by the observed MaxRanges value. Therefore MaxRanges=8 excludes successful Range10/K_AES Range10 operations or exact GetACL responses, MaxRanges=10 does not exclude Range10 when the row/key is present, and any earlier successful observation of Range10 makes a later successful LockingInfo.Get reporting MaxRanges=8 inconsistent.",
