        "opal/4.2.1.6.txt",
        "opal/4.3.1.6.txt",
        "opal/4.3.1.7.txt",
        rule="GetACL identifies one concrete AccessControl association by InvokingID and MethodID and returns that row's ACL column as ACE uidrefs. The Core object_ref and method object reference syntax permits equivalent encodings of the same object or method, including UID strings, object/name dictionaries, and singleton wrappers. Those syntactic forms must normalize to the same InvokingID/MethodID association, while exact ACL comparison still rejects omitted or wrong ACE uidrefs.",
