        "opal/4.3.5.2.1.2.txt",
        rule="CreateRow on the Locking table creates a non-global Locking object only when the requested range satisfies the non-overlap and alignment rules; failed CreateRow invocations do not create a row or reserve the requested LBAs. DeleteRow deletes the selected object-table row, so its LBA range no longer participates in later overlap checks and may be reused by a later valid CreateRow.",
